<ul>
    <li><strong>Never Taught This:</strong> Graduate programs don't teach systems leadership. Most supervision focuses on clinical skills, not district-wide impact.</li>
    <li><strong>The Isolation Problem:</strong> Without mentorship or community, most BCBAs reinvent the wheel alone—making the same mistakes others have already solved.</li>
    <li><strong>Fear of Change:</strong> Shifting from "helpful expert" to "systems builder" feels uncomfortable at first. It requires letting go of being the hero.</li>
    <li><strong>The Real Question:</strong> What's the cost of staying stuck? Burnout, turnover, and kids who don't get the support they need.</li>
</ul>
